:: Hallway
{set $visited_rooms = $visited_rooms + 1}
The hallway stretches in both directions, lit by torches mounted on the stone walls.

Rooms visited: {print $visited_rooms}

To the left, you hear faint music. To the right, silence.


[[Go left toward the music|Music Room]]

[[Go right into silence|Dark Corridor]]

[[Go back to the room|Start]]

:: Room
{set $visited_rooms = $visited_rooms + 1}
The room is small and bare. A straw mattress lies in one corner. On a wooden table, you find a rusty key and a folded note.


{if $has_key}
  You already have the key.
{else}
  [[Take the key|Take Key]]
{/if}

{if $has_note}
  You've already read the note.
{else}
  [[Read the note|Note]]
{/if}

[[Go to the door|Hallway]]

:: Take Key
{set $has_key = true}
You pick up the rusty key. It's cold and heavy.


[[Go back|Room]]

:: Note
{set $has_note = true}
The note reads:

"The music holds the answer. The silence holds the key. Neither path is wrong, but only one is free."


[[Put the note down|Room]]

:: Music Room [music]
{set $visited_rooms = $visited_rooms + 1}
A grand piano sits in the center of a circular room. The music you heard was coming from... nowhere. The piano sits untouched, yet the melody continues.


[[Sit at the piano|Piano]]

[[Go back to the hallway|Hallway]]

:: Dark Corridor [dark]
{set $visited_rooms = $visited_rooms + 1}
{do}$player.damage(10){/do}
The corridor grows darker with each step. Your footsteps echo off unseen walls. You stumble and hurt yourself.

Health: {$player.hp}/{$player.maxHp} — {$player.healthStatus}

{if $player.isDead}
  You collapse. Everything goes dark...
  [[Darkness...|Game Over]]
{else}
  {if $player.hp < 50}
    You feel weak and dizzy.
  {elseif $player.hp < 80}
    You wince in pain but press on.
  {else}
    You press on bravely.
  {/if}

  You reach a dead end. But wait — there's a small lever on the wall.


  {if $has_key}
    [[Use the key on the lock|Secret Room]]

  {/if}
  [[Pull the lever|Secret Room]]

  [[Go back|Hallway]]
{/if}


:: Piano [music]
As your fingers touch the keys, the melody shifts. The walls seem to breathe. A doorway of light opens behind the piano.


[[Step through the light|Ending]]

[[Stop playing|Music Room]]

:: Secret Room [dark secret]
{set $visited_rooms = $visited_rooms + 1}
The wall slides open to reveal a small chamber. In its center, a crystal orb pulses with soft blue light.


[[Touch the orb|Ending]]

[[Leave it alone|Dark Corridor]]

:: Game Over [ending]
You have fallen, {$player.name}.

Your body lies still in the dark corridor. The torches flicker and die.

Final rooms visited: {$visited_rooms}

THE END

[[Try again|Start]]

:: Ending [ending]
A warm light envelops you. When it fades, you find yourself standing in a sunlit meadow.

You are free, {$player.name}.

Final health: {$player.hp}/{$player.maxHp}

Rooms visited: {$visited_rooms}

{if $player.hp >= $player.maxHp}
  You escaped unscathed!
{elseif $player.hp >= 50}
  You made it out, a little worse for wear.
{else}
  You barely survived, but you're free.
{/if}


THE END

[[Play again|Start]]

:: Macro Demo
{set _temp = "hello"}
{do}
$demo_ran = true
{/do}
This passage demonstrates all macros.


Reactivity — press the button to increment the counter:

Count: {$count} {if $count < 10}{button $count = $count + 1}+1{/button}{else}[[You reached 10! Continue->Start]]{/if}

Unlike traditional Twine formats that re-render the entire passage, only the count and the button area above re-render. Everything else on the page stays untouched.


Variable display: {$player.name}

Temporary variable: {_temp}

Computed expression: {print $player.hp * 2}

Player status: {$player.healthStatus}


Health: {$player.hp}/{$player.maxHp} —
{.green if $player.hp >= $player.maxHp}
  Full health!
{.green-yellow elseif $player.hp >= 50}
  Doing okay.
{.red-yellow elseif $player.hp > 0}
  Need healing!
{.red else}
  You died!
{/if}


{if $player.hp > 0}
  {.red button $player.damage(10)}Drink Poison{/button}
{/if}
{if $player.hp < $player.maxHp}
  {.green button $player.heal(10)}Drink Health potion{/button}
{/if}


Inventory ({print $inventory.length} items):

{for @item, @i of $inventory}
  {print @i + 1}. {@item}
{/for}


{if $demo_ran}The do-block executed successfully.{/if}



CSS class syntax:

{.hero-name $player.name} — variable with class

{.muted print $visited_rooms} — print with class

{.highlight if $player.hp < 50}You're hurt!{/if} — if with class

{.danger button $player.damage(10)}Take 10 (styled){/button} — button with class

[[.fancy Back to start|Start]] — link with class

{.danger.large button $player.damage(5)}Multi-class button{/button} — multiple classes


All link syntaxes:

- Pipe: [[Back to start|Start]]

- Arrow: [[Arrow to hallway->Hallway]]

- Reverse arrow: [[Room<-Visit the room]]

- Plain: [[Start]]




:: Markdown Demo
# Markdown Support

This passage demonstrates **CommonMark markdown** rendering in Spindle.

## Text Formatting

You can use **bold**, *italic*, ~~strikethrough~~, and `inline code`.

## Lists

Unordered:
- Sword of Truth
- Shield of Valor
- Potion of Healing

Ordered:
1. Enter the dungeon
2. Find the treasure
3. Escape alive

## Blockquote

> "Not all those who wander are lost."
> — J.R.R. Tolkien

## Code Block

```
{set $player.hp = 100}
{if $player.hp > 50}
  You feel strong.
{/if}
```

## Table

| Stat | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Health | {$player.hp}/{$player.maxHp} |
| Strength | {$player.strength} |
| Dexterity | {$player.dexterity} |

## Horizontal Rule

---

Mixed with Twine syntax: your name is **{$player.name}** and you have {$player.hp} HP.

